narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: HSHM 411 is a really interesting seminar, especially for science majors who want to know more about the history of physical science.
I would recommend HIST 141J to any STEM major. It is very interesting and worth your time.

It was a very interesting class on the history of physical sciences. There is very little work in the course, only 2 papers and one time leading discussion the entire semester. Good class to take if interested in the topic.
